		<category><![CDATA[Lebanon]]></category>

		<category><![CDATA[Salafis]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.jihadica.com/?p=198</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Lebanon that is.  Over the past few days, there has been fighting between the Jabal Muhsin and Bab al-Tabbana neighborhoods that has killed a handful of people and injured dozens.  The former is predominantly Alawi and the latter is Sunni.
The clash has prompted confused speculation on Ekhlaas.  No one is sure who [...]<script type="text/javascript">SHARETHIS.addEntry({ title: "Trouble in Tripoli", url: "http://www.jihadica.com/trouble-in-tripoli/" });</script>]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Lebanon that is.  Over the past few days, there has been fighting between the Jabal Muhsin and Bab al-Tabbana neighborhoods that has killed a handful of people and injured dozens.  The former is predominantly Alawi and the latter is Sunni.</p>
<p>The clash has prompted confused speculation on Ekhlaas.  No one is sure who is fighting or who to root for. Abu_3ubayda puts it best when he says, &#8220;The resistance now is spontaneous and unorganized. What has happened so far is improvised.&#8221;</p>
<p>One point of contention is the extent of <a onclick="urchinTracker('/outgoing/www.ipsnews.net/news.asp?idnews=43173&referer=');urchinTracker('/outgoing/www.ipsnews.net/news.asp?idnews=43173&amp;referer=http://www.jihadica.com/wp-admin/edit.php');urchinTracker('/outgoing/www.ipsnews.net/news.asp?idnews=43173&amp;referer=http://www.jihadica.com/wp-admin/post.php?action=edit&amp;post=198&amp;message=4');urchinTracker('/outgoing/www.ipsnews.net/news.asp?idnews=43173&amp;referer=http://www.jihadica.com/wp-admin/post-new.php');" href="http://www.ipsnews.net/news.asp?idnews=43173">Salafi involvement</a>.  Some members say that most of the Sunnis fighting are Salafis, while others deny it.</p>
<p>Bab al-Tabbana is said to be a stronghold of Salafism in Tripoli, where the puritanical Sunni movement has become powerful, if fractured, in recent years.  Still, <a onclick="urchinTracker('/outgoing/yalibnan.com/site/archives/2008/06/analysi_fears_o.php?referer=');urchinTracker('/outgoing/yalibnan.com/site/archives/2008/06/analysi_fears_o.php?referer=http://www.jihadica.com/wp-admin/edit.php');urchinTracker('/outgoing/yalibnan.com/site/archives/2008/06/analysi_fears_o.php?referer=http://www.jihadica.com/wp-admin/post.php?action=edit&amp;post=198&amp;message=4');urchinTracker('/outgoing/yalibnan.com/site/archives/2008/06/analysi_fears_o.php?referer=http://www.jihadica.com/wp-admin/post-new.php');" href="http://yalibnan.com/site/archives/2008/06/analysi_fears_o.php">not every Sunni taking up arms</a> in the neighborhood identifies as a Salafi.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.jihadica.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/07/militans-in-tripoli.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-199" title="militans-in-tripoli" src="http://www.jihadica.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/07/militans-in-tripoli.jpg" alt="" width="292" height="219" /></a></p>
<p>Document (Arabic): <a href="http://www.jihadica.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/07/7-10-08-ekhlaas-truth-of-battle-between-sunnis-and-alawis-in-northern-lebanon.pdf">7-10-08-ekhlaas-truth-of-battle-between-sunnis-and-alawis-in-northern-lebanon</a><a href="http://www.jihadica.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/07/7-10-08-ekhlaas-truth-of-battle-between-sunnis-and-alawis-in-northern-lebanon.pdf"></a></p>
<p><a href="http://sharethis.com/item?&wp=2.5.1&amp;publisher=adab62c7-0bc6-488f-832a-aab9e4abcf47&amp;title=Trouble+in+Tripoli&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.jihadica.com%2Ftrouble-in-tripoli%2F" onclick="urchinTracker('/outgoing/sharethis.com/item?_wp=2.5.1_amp_publisher=adab62c7-0bc6-488f-832a-aab9e4abcf47_amp_title=Trouble+in+Tripoli_amp_url=http_3A_2F_2Fwww.jihadica.com_2Ftrouble-in-tripoli_2F&referer=');">ShareThis</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
